132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1644
S.P. 652 In Senate, April 15, 2025
An Act to Require Train Axle Bearing Sensors to Be Installed on
Passenger Rail Lines
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on April 11, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Transportation pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator RAFFERTY of York.
Cosponsored by Representative CROCKETT of Portland and
Senator: INGWERSEN of York, Representatives: DODGE of Belfast, MITCHELL of
Cumberland, SAYRE of Kennebunk.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 23 MRSA §7016 is enacted to read:
3 §7016. Hotbox detectors
4 Beginning January 1, 2027, a hotbox detector must be installed every 20 miles on a
5 railroad line that operates in the State on which a passenger train operates. For purposes
6 of this section, "hotbox detector" means a system of sensors that monitor and identify
7 overheated axle bearings of a train using an infrared thermal detection system as wheelsets
8 pass over the detector.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill requires the installation of a hotbox detector every 20 miles on a railroad line
1111 that operates in the State on which a passenger train operates, beginning January 1, 2027.
